##Integrating MATLAB with Arduino

MATLAB as the brain (PC controls the Arduino over USB)
Great for prototyping, logging and plotting without rewriting Arduino code.

What I installed
- MATLAB + the MATLAB Support Package for Arduino Hardware
  (MATLAB → Home → Add-Ons → Get Hardware Support Packages)

What it does
- MATLAB opens a live connection to the board,
- reads the ultrasonic sensor,
- drives the servo,
- and plots angle–distance in real time.

Minimal MATLAB script
---matlab
% Connect (adjust 'Uno' if you use a different board)
a   = arduino('COM3','Uno','Libraries',{'Servo','Ultrasonic'});
son = ultrasonic(a,'D9','D10');     % TRIG = D9, ECHO = D10
srv = servo(a,'D3');                % servo signal on D3

angles = 0:2:180;                   % sweep step (degrees)
figure; pol = polarplot(0,0); rlim([0 4]); % meters (HC-SR04 ~0.02–4m)

for k = [angles, fliplr(angles)]
    writePosition(srv, k/180);      % 0..1 maps to 0..180 deg
    pause(0.03);                    % let servo settle
    d = readDistance(son);          % meters
    set(pol,'ThetaData',deg2rad(k),'RData',min(d,4));
    drawnow;
end

clear a
----
